##Full text | announcement of the findings by Li Wenliang

Wechat, chinanewsweekly

Function introduction, here is "China News weekly" the head of the weekly gentleman, the influence has the influence you. Come with me to clear the fog, to seek the truth, to watch the Times.

Urge the Public Security Bureau to rescind the reprimand and hold the person responsible

On February 7,2020, the State Supervision and Administration Commission set up an investigation team to carry out an investigation in accordance with the law into the situation reported by the public concerning Dr. Li Wenliang. The investigation is being reported as follows.

The basic information of Dr. Li Wenliang and the background and process of forwarding and publishing information about wechat

Li Wenliang, Male, Manchu, born in October 1985 in Jinzhou, Liaoning Province, a member of the Chinese Communist Party, died on February 7,2020, of pneumonia caused by a COVID-19 infection at work. He was an ophthalmologist at Wuhan Central Hospital.

In December 2019, some patients with pneumonia of unknown cause were admitted to Hubei Integrated Traditional Chinese and Western Medicine Hospital, Back Lake Hospital area of Wuhan Central Hospital and Wuhan Red Cross Hospital. On December 27, Zhang Jixian, head of respiratory and Critical Care Medicine Department at Hubei Integrated Traditional Chinese and Western Medicine Hospital, reported to the hospital three cases of pneumonia of unknown cause, which were reported to Kong Hon District Center for Disease Control and Prevention in Wuhan. On the same day, the Wuhan Center for Disease Control arranged for the three patients to do an epidemiological investigation and testing. On December 29, the Hubei Integrated Traditional Chinese and Western Medicine Hospital reported another 4 cases of pneumonia of unknown origin from the South China Seafood Market. Wuhan Health Commission organized a team of experts to investigate, the same night the relevant patients were referred to Wuhan Jinyintan Hospital. Considering that similar cases have been found in many hospitals throughout the city, on December 30,15:10 and 8:50 respectively, the Wuhan Municipal Commission of Health and hygiene issued the departmental document "emergency notice on reporting the situation of the treatment of pneumonia of unknown cause" and "emergency notice on doing well the work of the treatment of pneumonia of unknown cause" within the system, we need to do a good job in the treatment of pneumonia of unknown cause and conduct a comprehensive search and retrospective investigation of pneumonia cases related to the south China Seafood Market. The two notices were uploaded to the Internet at 15:22 and around 19:00 on the same day.

At about 17:30 on December 30,2019, Dr. Li Wenliang received a message from a colleague. At 17:43, dr Li Wenliang, nicknamed "Li Wenliang, Wuhan, ophthalmology" on Wechat Group's "Wuhan University 04 Clinical Level" , forwarded and posted text messages such as "seven cases of SARS have been diagnosed in the south China fruit and Seafood Market" , "quarantine in the emergency department of the Back Lake District of our hospital" and a picture of the results of a clinical pathogen screening with the words "SARS coronavirus detection (high confidence) " and an 11-second lung CT video. At 18:42, the group also posted "the latest news is that the coronavirus infection has been confirmed, virus typing is being carried out" "everyone do not spread, let family members pay attention to prevent" . Similar messages have also appeared on other wechat groups. Wuhan Health Commission was uploaded to the Internet two departmental documents, and Dr. Li Wenliang and other people forwarded, published information, cause concern and discussion.

2. Dr. Li Wenliang's Public Security Bureau interview, Disciplinary Interview and hospital interview

At 13:38 on December 31,2019, the Wuhan Municipal Health and Health Commission issued a "circular on the current situation of pneumonia in our city, " saying that "27 cases have been found" and "the above-mentioned cases are viral pneumonia. " "So far, no significant human-to-human transmission has been found in the investigation, and no infection among medical staff has been found, " he said. Several media outlets have reported on it. In accordance with Wuhan's work arrangements on the prevention and control of pneumonia of unknown cause, Wuhan's public security organs, in accordance with the laws and regulations on the prevention and control of infectious diseases, public security management, and the notification of the Municipal Health and Health Commission, the situation of retransmitting and publishing information about SARS and other infectious diseases on the Internet was investigated and dealt with. At about 13:30 on January 3,2020, the police station of Zhongnan Road, Wuchang Branch of the Wuhan Public Security Bureau, contacted Li Wenliang, who came to the police station accompanied by a colleague. Police Station Deputy Director Yang arrangement responsible for the internal work of the police Hu and Dr. Li Wenliang Talk. After the interview was verified, the interviewee made a statement on the spot. Dr. Li Wenliang said it was wrong to send information about SARS in the wechat group, and would pay attention in the future. The interviewer made a warning letter to Dr. Li Wenliang. Dr Li Wenliang also held a letter of caution and left the police station at around 14:30. The interviewers were Hu and an auxiliary police officer. Hu signed his own name and the name of the police officer on duty that day. In fact, Xu did not participate in the conversation.

On the morning of December 31,2019, after a message posted by Dr. Li Wenliang on his wechat group was widely reposted on the Internet, relevant leaders of Wuhan Central Hospital had a conversation with Dr. Li Wenliang. Dr. Li Wenliang said in the conversation that he forwarded unverified information about SARS to the students in the group in order to remind them to take precautions. The hospital asked Dr. Li Wenliang to write an understanding material. Until Dr. Li was hospitalized, he had been working as an ophthalmologist in the hospital as usual.

III. Dr. Li Wenliang's illness, treatment and emergency treatment

Dr Lee man-leung developed fever on 10 January 2020 and was admitted to the ophthalmology ward of Wuhan Central Hospital on 12 January, transferred to the third ward of respiratory and critical care medicine on 14 January and transferred to the intensive-care unit of respiratory and critical care medicine on 23 January, died on February 7th.

On December 9,2019, Dr. Li Wenliang was transferred from the OPHTHALMIC clinic to the OPHTHALMIC Ward. On January 6,2020, Dr. Li Wenliang admitted an 82-year-old eye patient. The patient developed fever on January 7 and was subsequently confirmed to have novel coronavirus. He passed away on January 23. On January 10, Li Wenliang developed fever and attended the fever clinic of Wuhan Central Hospital.

On January 12, Li Wenliang was admitted to area 2 Ophthalmology Department of Wuhan General Hospital. His diagnosis was acute conjunctivitis and pulmonary infection in his right eye. On January 14, Li Wenliang was transferred to a respiratory ward in zone 3 with increased bilateral infection. Dr. Li wen-liang was placed in single-room isolation in the three zones of aspiration, and specialized nursing staff were arranged to take shifts to monitor Oxygenation, heart rate and blood pressure immediately, and he was given aspiration support and symptomatic support treatment such as anti-virus, anti-infection, expectoration and stomach protection, use Steroids and Gamma Globulin. From January 15 to January 18, according to Li Wenliang's condition, the attending doctor adjusted the medicine and treatment in a timely manner.

On January 19, Dr. Li Wenliang had intermittent fever. In the afternoon, the hospital aspiration and critical care division chief physician, New Pneumonia Hospital Medical Treatment Expert Group leader to see Dr. Li Wenliang condition, treatment advice. In the evening, the hospital asked the Huazhong University of Science and Technology to consult Dr Li Wenliang, who is a professor of respiratory and critical care medicine and the head of the new Wuhan Pneumonia Expert Group.

From January 20 to 22, Li Wenliang did not have fever, but his asthma symptoms remained severe. On January 15,19,20,21, new champion Pneumonia Hospital Medical Treatment Expert Group leader, Deputy Group leader and other hospital experts to see Dr. Li Wenliang's condition and make diagnosis and treatment advice.

At about 23:50 on January 22, Dr. Li Wenliang developed breathing and dyspnea after going to the toilet. The Oxygenation rate dropped to 88% . After treatment, his symptoms eased slightly. The attending doctor again informed him of his serious condition and, with his consent, transferred him to the intensive-care unit at 3:30 a.m. on January 23.

Until January 27, most hospitals in Wuhan, including the city's Central Hospital, did not have the qualifications or the qualifications for nucleic acid testing. After upgrading the facility, on 27 January the Wuhan Central Hospital began a trial run of nucleic acid testing. On January 28 and January 31, the hospital tested Dr. Li's nucleic acid twice, the first time it was negative and the second time it was positive. On January 31, Dr Li Wenliang was confirmed to have contracted the new coronavirus.

From January 31 to February 3, Dr Li Wenliang was Febrile and had some relief from shortness of breath, but his spirit and appetite were poor. At noon on February 4, she presented with vomiting, frequent cough, aggravated wheezing, and relieved symptoms after treatment. On February 5, Dr. Li Wenliang had no fever, but still had wheezing and shortness of breath in resting state. The chest film beside the bed suggested that the right pneumonia was aggravated. On February 6, Dr. Li Wenliang had a serious lung condition that threatened to worsen. After the Expert Group consultation in the hospital, it was suggested that the hospital be transferred to the more professional Houhu hospital area. With the consent of Dr. Li Wenliang and his family, Dr. Li Wenliang was transferred to the hospital area at about 18:20, accompanied by the attending doctor and two nurses. At approximately 1855 hours, you will arrive at the back Lake area of Wuhan Central Hospital.

At 19:20 on February 6, Li Wenliang presented with mental block and progressive drop in heart rate and blood pressure. He was immediately injected with Epinephrine to strengthen the heart and open the blood vessel to increase blood pressure. Endotracheal intubation was performed simultaneously, and aspiration was maintained with continuous chest compressions. At 21:30, on the extracorporeal cardiopulmonary resuscitation instrument, assisted by continuous external chest cardiac compression, continue CPR, and give active drug resuscitation. At 22:40, Dr. Li Wenliang was treated with ECMO (extracorporeal membrane oxygenation machine, commonly known as "artificial lung") , which the hospital had borrowed from Wuhan Yaxin Hospital. Wuhan City Health Coordination, Peking Union Medical College Hospital experts rushed to the scene. At 2:58 a.m. on February 7, Li Wenliang was pronounced clinically dead after showing a LINEAR ECG response. At 3:48, the hospital announced the death of Dr. Li Wenliang.

The doctor who organized the rescue said, "Dr. Li Wenliang is our colleague and very young. We don't want him to go. As long as there is a little hope, we don't want to give up. At that time, we didn't think of any other factors, that is, we wanted to save him. " So it took a long time. The attending doctor of Li Wenliang said that although he could not save Li Wenliang's life, his treatment was standard, the rescue was timely and every effort was made. According to Dr. Li Wenliang consultation outside experts said, from Dr. Li Wenliang medical records, hospital treatment is relatively standard, according to the condition of drugs and measures. The hospital has consulted Dr. Li Wenliang or his family members on the important medical measures proposed and actually taken.

IV. Dr. Li Wenliang's post-death care and rehabilitation

After the death of Dr. Li Wenliang, Wuhan Central Hospital set up a special work class, fully responsible for the pension, aftercare work. On the afternoon of February 7, leaders of the City Center Hospital visited Dr. Li Wenliang's parents, wife and children. At the request of his wife, Li Wenliang arranged for her and the child to be recuperated in the hospital concerned.

Upon application by the Wuhan Central Hospital, the Human Resources and Social Security Bureau of Wuhan has determined that Li Wenliang was injured at work. In accordance with relevant regulations, death benefits have been paid in full and funeral benefits have been granted. The Insurance Company has paid out donated insurance to the family of Dr Li Wenliang, a front-line health care worker fighting the COVID-19 pneumonia epidemic. The Staff Union of the Wuhan Central Hospital has called on the staff to make donations for Li Wenliang and his family. The Wuhan Red Cross has received a targeted donation. All the donations have been passed on to the family of Li Wenliang. On March 4, the National Health Commission and other departments issued a decision to recognize advanced individuals in the national health care system for the prevention and control of the epidemic situation of new pneumonia, including Dr. Li Wenliang.

5. Work suggestions

As Zhongnan Road Police Station issued a letter of reprimand improperly, law enforcement procedures are not standardized, the investigation team has recommended that the Wuhan Supervisory Authority of Hubei Province supervise and rectify the matter, urge the Public Security Bureau to rescind the letter of reprimand and hold the personnel responsible, timely release of the results to the community.

Investigation team of the State Supervisory Committee

March 19,2020

Source: Xinhua News Agency
